--------------------------------------------- 1. systeminfo ----------------------------

- To get all the system info .

--------------------------------------------- 2. ver -----------------------------------------

- To get the version of Windows OS

--------------------------------------------- 3. dir -----------------------------------------

- To check current directory contents

--------------------------------------------- 4. C: ------------------------------------------

- to get into the c drive

----------------------------------------------5. mkdir folderName------------------------------------------------

- to create new folder in the current directory

----------------------------------------------6. cd .. ------------------------------------------------------

- to return into the parent folder

----------------------------------------------7. type nul > fileName.txt -----------------------------------

- to create a new file in current directory

----------------------------------------------8. del folderName/fileName -----------------------------------------------

- to delete the contents of folder(folder is made empty but not deleted )

-it deletes the file completely 


----------------------------------------------9. rmdir folderNAme --------------------------------------------

- to delete the folder completely

----------------------------------------------10. notepad/start fileName -----------------------------------------------

- to write in the file

----------------------------------------------11. copy file1 file2 ---------------------------------------------

- to copy contents of file1 to file2 also


----------------------------------------------12. type fileName -----------------------------------------------

- to see the file content(notepad content) in the prompt itself

























